\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0      Peruge shook his head from side to side. It was diabolic. A pack of amateurs would not have left \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 
this many loose ends and blunders behind them. Merrivale would admit no mistakes, though. And the man had those explicit orders to fall back on. Embarrassing. He would have to be shunted aside, though. He\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
d have to be stored somewhere, ready for the axe t\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 o\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 
 fall. Merrivale was a miserable incompetent. There was no excuse for him. He was just the kind of man they needed right now, someone to point to when the really embarrassing questions were asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0      With angry abruptness, Peruge pushed himself out of th\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 e chair, stood glowering down at Merrivale, who appeared thoroughly cowed.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re a fool, Merrivale,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Peruge said in a cold, hard voice. \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
ve always been a fool and always will be. We have a full report from DT on Tymiena\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s objections. She wanted \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 
a backup team. She wanted frequent radio contact. You specifically told her not to bother Portland-relay unless it was something vital. You told her she was to take her orders from Carlos and not to question them. You ordered her not to mount any official
\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 inquiry into Porter. Under no circumstances was she to move out from under her cover. Those were your instructions \hich\f0 \endash \'94\loch\f0  Peruge pointed to the folder on Merrivale\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s desk, \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 and you had read that!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0      Merrivale sat in shocked silence at the outburst. For one \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 
horrible moment, he appeared about to cry. His eyes glistened with unshed tears. Shocked awareness of that possibility cooled him, though, and he managed to respond with a semblance of his accent intact.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I say! You don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t leave your opinions in any do\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ubt!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Later, on the telephone from the airport, Peruge said, \'93\loch\f0 I suppose we ought to be grateful to him. There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s no doubt now of the situation we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
re in.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What do you mean by that?\'94\loch\f0  the Chief asked, his voice hoarsely disgruntled.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I mean, we\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0  went in not knowing Hellstrom\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s situation. Now, we know it. He\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s willing to play for high stakes.\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 As though we weren\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Well, I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve settled with Merrivale, at any rate. I ordered him to stand by for reassignment.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 He won\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t do anything s\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0 tupid?\'94
