\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 I think he\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll obey his orders to the letter,\'94\loch\f0  Peruge said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 But you upset him badly.\'94\loch\f0  It was a statement, not a question.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 No doubt of it.\'94\loch\f0  Thi\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 s was an unfamiliar tack, and Peruge hesitated, staring thoughtfully at his scrambler cap on the telephone.
