\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0      When the\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 y reached that point on the lower road where Peruge could get his first look at Hellstrom\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s farm, he asked Kraft to stop. The deputy brought his green and white station wagon to a skidding, dusty halt and peered questioningly at his passenger.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Someth\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ing wrong, Mr. Peruge?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Peruge merely tightened his lips. Kraft interested him. The deputy could have been typecast for the role he played. It was almost as though someone had looked at him and said, \'93\loch\f0 Now, this one, we
\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll make him the deputy.\'94\loch\f0  Kraft h\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 
ad a sunburned, western appearance, thick nose and beetling brows, pale yellow hair topped by a wide-brimmed western hat. His blocky features surmounted a blocky body that moved with a stiff-legged horseman\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s walk. Peruge had seen several people on Foster\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 v\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 ille\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s one main street who looked vaguely like Lincoln Kraft.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0      Kraft accepted Peruge\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s silent appraisal without qualms, secure in the knowledge that he was a Hive hybrid whose appearance could not possibly excite questions about alien background. Kraft
\loch\af0\dbch\af23\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s father had been a local rancher seduced in a gene-foray by a breeding female. Many Fosterville locals had remarked Kraft\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s resemblance to the father.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Now, Kraft cleared his throat. \'93\loch\f0 Mr. Peruge, I said \hich\f0 \endash \'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I know what you said.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0      Peruge gla\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 
nced at his wristwatch:  a quarter to three. Every delay imaginable had been thrown in the way of this excursion:  telephone calls, careful examination of the missing-persons report, a lengthy study of the photograph, question after question and a laborio
\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 u\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 s assemblage of answers on paper, all executed in a slow and meticulous longhand. But here they were, finally, in sight of Hellstrom\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s farm. Peruge felt his pulse quicken. The air carried a dry, cloying silence. Even the insects were still. Peruge sensed \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 s\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 
omething out of character about the stillness. He grew aware slowly of the absence of insect sounds and asked Kraft about this.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Kraft pushed his hat back, rubbed a sleeve across his forehead. \'93\loch\f0 I expect someone\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s used a spray.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Really? Does Hells\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0 trom do that sort of thing? I thought all the environmentalists were against sprays.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 How\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 d you know the doc was into ecology?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Sharp! Sharp! Peruge reminded himself. He said, \'93\loch\f0 I didn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t know it. I just assumed an entomologist would have that as \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0 one of his concerns.
\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Yeah? Well, maybe the doc isn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t spraying. This is rangeland right here.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Somebody else could be doing it?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Maybe. Or the doc could be doing something else. Did you have me stop just so you could listen?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 No. I \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 want to get out and scout around the area and see if I can spot any sign of Carlos\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s camper.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Not much sense in that.\'94\loch\f0  Kraft spoke quickly with an undertone of sharpness.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Oh? Why?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 If we decide he\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s really been around here, we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll do a tho\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0 rough search.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I thought I told you,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Peruge said. \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ve already decided he was around here. I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
d like to get out and have a little look at the area.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Doc don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t like people wandering around his place!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 But you said this was rangeland. Does\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0  he control it?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Not exactly, but \hich\f0 \endash \'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Then let\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s have a look.\'94\loch\f0  Peruge put a hand on the door.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 You just wait a minute!\'94\loch\f0  Kraft ordered.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0      Peruge nodded silently. He\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d found out what he wanted to know:  Kraft was here to block any investig\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 ation by strangers.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 All right,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Peruge said. \'93\loch\f0 Does Hellstrom know we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re coming?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0      Kraft had put the station wagon in gear, prepared to resume their lurching progress toward the farm, but now he hesitated. Peruge\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s demand that they stop had shocke\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 
d him. The first thought had been that the Outsider had seen something suspicious, something overlooked by the Hive\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s cleanup workers. Peruge\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s attempts to get out and search the area had done nothing to ease that initial disquiet. Now, it occurred to Kra\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 f\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 
t that Peruge or his people might have tapped the telephone to the farm. But Hive Security was always wary of that; surely they\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d have detected such intrusion.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Matter of fact, he does know,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Kraft said. \'93\loch\f0 I called to make sure the doc was here himself\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
. Sometimes he goes gadding off to mighty strange places. And I wanted to clear it that we were coming. You know how these scientists are.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 No. How are they?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 They do experiments sometimes. Outsiders go blundering in and upset everything.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0     \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0  \'93\loch\f0 Is that why you don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t want me to get out here?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Kraft spoke with obvious relief. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Sure it is. Besides, the doc makes movies up here all the time. He gets a bit testy if you ruin his pictures. We try to be good neighbors.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d think he\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d put \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0 out guards or something.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 No-o-o. The locals all know about his work. We steer clear of his place.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 How testy does he get if one ruins his experiments or his movies?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Peruge asked. \'93\loch\f0 Does he \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 \hich\f0  ahhh, shoot?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Nothing like that! Doc wouldn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 really hurt anybody. But he can be mighty rough mouthed when he wants. He\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
s got important friends, too. Pays to be on his good side.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0      That he has, Peruge thought. And that could explain the strange behavior of the local law. Kraft\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s job must be a sine\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 cure. He\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
d be careful not to lose it.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Peruge said, \'93\loch\f0 Okay. Let\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s go see if we can find Dr. Hellstrom\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s good side.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Yes, sir!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0      Kraft got the car moving, made a special effort to act casual and unconcerned. Hellstrom\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s orders had been explicit\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 
:  this was a routine investigation into some missing persons. All cooperation would be extended.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0      Peruge admired the farm buildings as they approached the north fence. The farm had been built in a time when materials were squandered without any worrie\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 s about the supply. There wasn\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 t a knot in any of the lumber visible on this side of the farmhouse or the barn, although the wood had that dark gray of long weathering and probably could have used a coat of paint. Peruge wondered idly why the farm wasn\hich\f0 \rquote 
\loch\f0 t \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 p\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 ainted.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Kraft stopped parallel to the fence, just clear of the gate. \'93\loch\f0 We walk from here. Doc doesn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t like us bringing cars up to the buildings.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Why\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s that?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Something to do with his work, I expect.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 The place could use a coat of pai\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0 nt,\'94\loch\f0  Peruge said as he got out of the car.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Kraft got out, closed the door, and spoke across the roof of the car. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
I heard tell Doc used some kind of wood preservative on his buildings. They just look weathered. Kind of pretty when you think about it.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Oh?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Peruge walked to the gate, waited for Kraft. \'93\loch\f0 What\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s that concrete building over there?\'94\loch\f0 
 He pointed to the low structure inside the fence to the left of the gate.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Might be a pumphouse. About the right size for a big one. Or it could be so\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 mething to do with the doc\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s work. I never asked.\'94\loch\f0 
 Kraft watched Peruge carefully. The concrete structure housed an emergency ventilation system which could be opened by explosives and was linked to standby pumping. There were several more such installati\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 o
\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 ns scattered around the area, but the others were camouflaged.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Is Hellstrom married?\'94\loch\f0  Peruge asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      Kraft opened the gate before answering. \'93\loch\f0 I don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t rightly know.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  He stood aside to let Peruge enter, closed the gate. \'93\loch\f0 
Doc has lots of pretty gals\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0  around here sometimes. For his movies, I s\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 pose. Maybe he thinks there\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s no sense buying a cow when milk\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s free.
\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Kraft chuckled at his own hairy witticism and added, \'93\loch\f0 Let\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s get along up to the farm.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0      Peruge shuddered as he fell into step with the de\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 
puty. That humor had been a little heavy. This deputy was neither pure western, pure yokel, nor pure anything else. Kraft tried too hard to appear the semirustic of earthy origins. The trying was so obvious at times that it dominated every other action. P
\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 e\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 ruge had decided earlier to watch the deputy carefully, but now he put an extra note of caution on his resolve.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Place looks kind of shabby,\'94\loch\f0  Peruge said, hurrying to keep pace with Kraft\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s long-legged stride. Despite the stiffness of his gait, the de
\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 puty moved with a no-loitering directness that suggested he didn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t want Peruge to take too close a look at the surroundings.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I thought it looked pretty good here,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Kraft said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 They keep the farm area pretty neat.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Do they do much farming?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0    \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0   \'93\loch\f0 Not much anymore. His folks used to keep a lot more crops. Some of the kids the doc has here plant corn and things in the spring, but they\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
re just playing at farming, seems to me. City people, most of them. They come up here from Hollywood or out from \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 N\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ew York and gawk at us natives and play farmer.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Hellstrom has a lot of visitors?\'94\loch\f0 
 Peruge kicked at a dusty clump of grass as he spoke. The dry, hot air of the place bothered him. There was an irritant humming sound in the background, and an underlyi\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 
ng animal smell that made him think of a zoo. This odor had not been apparent outside the fence, but it became stronger the deeper they went into the little valley. What he could see of the creek on his right showed only a thin trickle of water. It was mo
\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 s\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 tly pools and puddles connected by narrow rills full of green algae that waved in weak currents. There appeared to be a small waterfall at the upper end of the valley, however.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Visitors?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Kraft asked after a long pause. \'93\loch\f0 Sometimes the place is crawli\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 ng with \hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 em. Can\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 t spit without hitting someone. Other times, he probably doesn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t have more\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 n ten or twelve people here.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 What\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s that smell?\'94\loch\f0  Peruge demanded.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What smell?\'94\loch\f0  Kraft asked, then realized Peruge meant the Hive odor, most of which was\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 
 washed from the vented air but was always detectable here in the valley. Kraft rather enjoyed the odor. It reminded him of his childhood.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 That animal smell!\'94\loch\f0  Peruge said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0      \'93\loch\f0 Oh, that. Probably something to do with the doc\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s work. He keeps mice an\hich\af0\dbch\af23\loch\f0 \hich\f0 d things in cages up there. I saw them once. Regular menagerie.
\'94
